{
  "stem": "19690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 292.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But other than that, she was a wonderful grandmother and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a very giving person for everyone.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She was always the peacemaker in the family if anything went wrong.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Both of them were deported to Theresienstadt in July of 1942.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I've just recently found out through the Red Cross that they were then moved to southern Poland, to a camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my grandfather was seen working on a road gang by a neighbor from Speyer in 1943, in the spring.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this man spoke to him, and was sure that it was my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then they-- there is no other record of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The man told my cousin this after the war, when my cousin went to Speyer.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were wonderful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't like all the praying at home around the table.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my cousin and I would always do a lot of tomfoolery.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If we sat opposite each other, we would start giggling at each other on Shabbat or a Seder, when-- so my mother decided we would sit with an adult between us on one side of the table so we couldn't see each other.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we still managed to look down and look down and start trouble.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then we would get disciplined.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But in-- in the synagogue-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the synagogue was divided-- men downstairs, women upstairs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the children had a separate bench over on the side, next to the men.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was always opposite my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And anytime my dad felt that I was either being impatient or that I was starting to start something, he would signal me, here.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I would have to stand next to him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He-- the synagogue was very interesting.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
